<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://liquid2k.com/optica/images/neydor.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Profile</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Name: Neydor<br>
Age: 22<br>
Born: ?<br>
Weapons: Rune Sword, dagger<br>
Magical skill: various cantrips, and lower level spells, and possible spells stored within the sword.<br>
<br>
Background:<br>
Neydor was a promising hero in the kingdom in which he served; he was once the squire of the great knight Kaydar, and earned great reknown on the many adventures they shared. After his tutulege under the knight ended, he became a knight-errant of the Dragon King's court and was on his way to a glorious knightship. After the death of his love, a thief he adventured with in his squire days, he grew jaded and abandoned his duty and king in search of solace and peace. Wandering the known world --and stumbling upon foreign planes-- he rediscovered the talents he once neglected: magic (as a child, he was tested for a mentorship with a sage, but failed horribly). Using the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Rune Sword</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> forged by old dwarven friends, he can augment his spells into the blade. Coupled with his training in swordplay, he can unleash elemental magicks without expending much of his own mana. The rune sword powers much of his martial attacks (limited flight, speed, reflex) and has the random chance of deflection/absorption of hostile energies. <br>
Neydor is not a true mage, and in most circles, seen as a rogue mage and a considerable threat. Hearing of the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Gala</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, he journeyed to the event in hopes of finding the hidden artifact...and possibly the power to grant his heart's desire... <p><a href="http://www.liquid2k.com/optica">
