<br>
Now, a few provisions:<br>
---------------------------<br>
-I notice that there seems to be some &quot;base&quot; disciplines and ones that &quot;flavor&quot; others: an elemental conjurer or an illusionary necromancer.<br>
For now, I'll say, you can mix &amp; match no more than TWO disciplines:<br>
-The two disciplines CAN'T be the same thing.  A enchanter-enchanter sounds silly!<br>
-Stacking the deck with equally powerful disciplines won't fly.  One has to be the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> primary</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, the other secondary-- the monk w/ the elemental summons is good, but if he's adept at summoning the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Ultimate Fire God</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, that puts too quick an end to this little battle (not to mention, I'd be one to say he'd pop like a balloon fulla hydrogen trying to summon it!  IF he succeeded!)<br>
In this instance, I have three elemental conjurers, one for each of the &quot;negative&quot; elements.  You'll see who steps up to the plate tommorow!<br>
-------------------------------<br>
As for the Gala itself, I'll have a map ready very soon; I just need to nail down a few locales I'm not too clear on.<br>
It's going to be like a huge scavenger hunt, where mage teams are scaling the whole mountain &amp; several parties can run afoul of each other.  I'm not making it a point to have any monsters outside of what's been summoned... but it's funny to think if someone fouls up, a peculiar beast may show up!<br>
<br>
I'm doing a flip of the coin to make all my judgments; you'll see how it plays into the introduction.  It's also what I'm using to determine who wins the &quot;first bout&quot;, so it can go either way!  <br>
<br>
V1S1ON!  We need your sketch!  Same for Xiaoyue, if interested.  I think for now, that will do for entrants; <br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> four entrants, four &quot;champions&quot;; good amount of interplay!</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
If someone else wants in, the first has to be deposed!<br>
